# Manual Test Admin 001

## Test Case ID
`TC-ADMIN-001`

## Title
Manage Campaigns as Admin

## Tested By
`<Tester Name>`

## Test Date
`YYYY-MM-DD`

## Summary
Log in as an admin and manage campaigns by adding an active campaign, editing it, and deleting it.

## Preconditions
Empty database

## Test Steps
1. Open to the admin login and enter the username admin and password admin
2. Select the campaigns section and select add campaign.
3. Enter the test data for the campaign
4. Select save
5. Navigate to the map page and click on the campaign banner
6. Navigate to admin console
7. Select the campaign that was just added and edit with the edited test data
8. Navigate to map page and click on campaign banner
9. Navigate to admin console
10. Select the campaign that was added and delete it
11. Navigate to map page

## Test Data
*start and end time are relative to the time that the tester is creating the campaigns*

Initial Campaign:
Name: Netherlands Water Week
Description: Celebrate water week in the netherlands by recording water temperature data
Start time: today and now
End time: one week from today and now
Region: Select entire netherlands

Edited Campaign (only changed fields included):
Name: Netherlands Water Day
Description: Celebrate water day in the netherlands by recording water temperature data
End time: tomorrow and now

## Expected Result
Admin console:
- Upon adding the campaign, it should appear in the database and also be visible on the admin console
- Edits to the campaign should also be reflected in the admin console and database
- Once the campaign is deleted, it should disappear from the admin console and database.
- There should be a prompt when deleting the campaign that confirms this action
Map page:
- The initial campaign should appear on the map page as a banner with displaying the data that was mentioned in the test data section
- Once edited, the campaign should still appear on the map page as a banner with a countdown of about a day and the changes reflected in the title and description
- Once deleted, the map page should display no campaign banner

